# SqlTxt.Storage

On-disk persistence with human-readable text formats. Cross-platform (Windows, macOS, Linux).

## Directory Layout

```
<DatabaseName>/                    # Root folder = database name
  db/                              # Database descriptor and properties
    manifest.json
  Tables/                          # User tables
    <TableName>/
      <TableName>.txt              # Root data file
      <TableName>_PK.txt           # Primary key (Phase 2+)
      <TableName>_FK_<LinkedTable>.txt   # Foreign key (Phase 2+)
      <TableName>_INX_<Columns>_<N>.txt # Index (Phase 2+)
  Views/                           # Views (late-project)
  Procedures/                      # Stored procedures (advanced SQL)
  Functions/                       # User-defined functions (advanced SQL)
  ~System/                         # System-generated; meta-information
```

## System Folder Prefix

The `~` character prefixes system-generated folders (e.g., `~System`). Valid on Windows, macOS, Linux. Use for engine-managed folders.

## File Formats

- **manifest.json** — Engine version, storage format version
- **Root data** — Fixed-width positional rows with soft-delete marker (A| or D|)
- **PK/FK/INX files** — Index structures (Phase 2+)

## Guidelines

- Use `IFileSystemAccessor` to abstract file I/O for testability.
- Implement `ISchemaStore`, `ITableDataStore`, `IMetadataStore`.
- Support format versioning for future evolution.
- All file/folder names must be valid on Windows, macOS, and Linux.
